    <!-- Translation notes -->
    <h3>Translation notes</h3>
    <p>The convex hull algorithm shown is Jarvis march (gift wrapping), which runs in O(nh) time where h is the number of hull vertices. Graham scan achieves O(n log n) regardless of output size. The separation theorem stated here is the finite-dimensional version; the infinite-dimensional generalization (Hahn-Banach) requires additional hypotheses (closedness, or one set having nonempty interior).</p>

